rest_of_day_open: Tomorrow, I have to go to the hospital to have a test and I feel a lot of stress about that. I am concerned about exposure to COVID-19 and I think that the etest itself will be uncomfortable. So, I think that the start of the week ahead after this day will be filled with anxiety and then a nagging fear that I could have been exposed to a potentially deadly virus will continue for up to two weeks after that. I think I'll go about my normal life (cooking, cleaning, writing, etc.) for the most part except for that anxiety. I also am looking forward to the holiday ahead and my husband being home more than usual.
critical_positive: I think that my conversation partner responded well to my questions, but showed little interest in me or my life. She asked me no questions and I could see in her eyes that she was checking out when I spoke about myself. So, I think that her replies to my questions worked well toward giving me the ability to ask follow-up questions.
critical_negative: As I said before, my partner clearly wasn't interested in me or my life. I think she either wasn't interested in me because of our age difference, or she's only doing these conversations for the payment and not really to engage with the other person. I felt that her social skills were more oriented toward talking about herself than learning about other people.

rest_of_day_open: The rest of my week will be a bit stressful as I rush to get everything ready for a small Thanksgiving get-together at my home that I do not want to happen. I don't think it is a good idea at all but my boyfriend's family pushed for it and I got forced into it. I plan to stay away from everyone but will feel uncomfortable in my own home because of COVID, and I am already stressed and trying to proactively get my cleaning supplies ready to disinfect the moment they all leave.
critical_positive: We had some of the same hobbies and are both interested in picking up more work from home freelance work. She was very friendly and talkative and seemed to enjoy both talking about herself and listening to me talk about my life as well. She made sure to keep the conversation flowing with me but not interrupt or cut in.
critical_negative: We live on opposite sides of the country and our ages were different, though that really didn't affect the conversation too negatively. She did like to start a lot of the conversation topics, but as someone who tends to be quieter when first meeting someone I didn't mind at all.
